translated:
Karl Albert, former senior physician, Gothenburg, born on 1/6/72 in Gothenburg to city district physician Lars August Theoidor W. and Anna Emfrida Mathilda Almiberg. Married 10 times to Lida Böving. - Completed secondary education in Gothenburg in 1990, received a Bachelor's degree in Medicine in 1996 and a medical license in 2003 from Uppsala University. Assistant and trainee at the national institute in Uppsala 94-95, at the surgical clinic there 98-99, trainee at the surgical outpatient clinic 99-00, assistant and examiner at the pathology institute from 2000, assistant at the surgical clinic from 2003, sub-surgeon there from 2004, trainee at Sahligr. hospital surgical and medical department from 2005, acting deputy surgeon at the surgical department there 05-06, deputy physician there 06-10, including three months as acting senior physician. Senior physician at Ekmanska hospital 10-37, general practitioner. Hobby: philately. Recipient of Royal Order of the North Star, Helsingborg Medal of Honor in Uppsala, and Uppland Shooting Association Gold medal, Shooting Gold Medal. 

Arvid Edvard; clergyman, Åled, born on 31/08/89 in Gothenburg to Edvard W. and Alma Holmstedt. Married 27 times to Märtha Olsson. Two children: Gunnel and Ulla born in 1934. Completed secondary education in Gothenburg in 1909, passed a Latin exam in 1914, received a degree in Philosophy in Theology in 1914, passed a theology exam and practical theology test in 1919, ordained as a priest for the Gothenburg diocese in 1920. Served as pastoral assistant in Morlanda, Örby, Harplinge, and as a pastor in Harplinge, Hjärtum, Bollebygd, Getinge, Årstads, Sätila, Eldsberga, among others, and as a church assistant in Forsbälila and Hjärtum, church official in Enslöv since 1941.
